$y=-2\cos^2 x -\cos x +3.$$\\$
Đặt $t= \cos x \in [-1;1]$, ta được
\begin{align*}
y=f(t)&=-2t^2-t+3\\
f'(t)&=-4t-1\\
f'(t)&=0 \Leftrightarrow t=-\dfrac{1}{4}
\end{align*}
Có $f(-1)=2;\; f(1)=0;\; f\left(-\dfrac{1}{4}\right)=\dfrac{25}{8}.$
Vậy $M=\dfrac{25}{8}$, $m=0$. Do đó $M\cdot n =0$

Ta có: $\mathscr{D}=\left[3;5\right]$; $y'=\dfrac{1}{2\sqrt{x-3}}-\dfrac{1}{2\sqrt{5-x}}=\dfrac{\sqrt{5-x}-\sqrt{x-3}}{2\sqrt{5 - x} \sqrt{x - 3}}$ ;
		$y'=0\Leftrightarrow x=4$.$\\$
		$y(3)=y(5)=\sqrt{2}$, $y(4)=2$. Suy ra: $T=\left[\sqrt{2};2\right]$
